20 Jul 2012 20:08






I also agree that the  to make it clear that the B-class was directly referencing Muldoon. The man has probably seen Jurassic Park, so he'd probably have trouble using the phrase unironically anyway.

But I really enjoyed this log, and it made me enjoy the main SCP even more than before. I like the idea that the Foundation is now essentially containing an entire alien environment on its grounds.

I'd love to see Beta-class become more of a thing, too. The Foundation should be pragmatic before anything else, and losing valuable personnel whose skillsets don't come along every day combined with extensive and effective on-the-job training just so that you can adhere rigidly to protocol is not very pragmatic.







